Similarly, it is normally a requirement in mergers for the selling sharehol=
ders to get to vote on the deal: They own the company, after all, and it ca=
n=E2=80=99t be bought from them without their permission. But in a distress=
ed bank merger it is silly to pretend that the shareholders own the company=
