<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Oh, fine, I understand the position a little. =
The position is =E2=80=9Cbonds are senior to stock.=E2=80=9D The AT1s are b=
onds, so people bought them expecting them to get paid ahead of the stock i=
n every scenario. They ignored the fact that=C2=A0<em>it was crystal clear =
from the terms of the AT1 contract and even from the name=C2=A0</em>that th=
